  "body": "### Description\n\nDev services usually use testcontainers in the background to spin up a service. Testcontainers has a default timeout of 60 seconds to wait for a container to become ready. In slow CI setups, this timeout might be too narrow. In our case, pulling Keycloak on a runner node and subsequently starting the heavy weight JBoss container takes more than 60 seconds. Unfortunately, there doesn't seem to be an option to control this timeout apart from a code instruction `withStartupTimeout` (https://www.testcontainers.org/features/startup_and_waits/).\r\n\r\nAs on some systems the default 60 seconds wait time are too low, please provide an option to increase this timeout for dev services based on testcontainers.\n\n### Implementation ideas\n\nMaybe this should be phrased generically, because most dev services are based on testcontainers. Something like `quarkus.dev-services.container-timeout` would be nice, respected by all dev services.",
